# {{AU}} Australian Eastern Daylight Time
Australian Eastern Daylight Time is applies to Queensland Australia. The normal eastern time is simply put 2 hours forward to obtain more daylight during the evenings. The reason is so both international visitors and locals can enjoy the great outdoors during the evenings in daylight. AEDT has been set as of 01.01.2006 and is a fixed time setting, which means it does not get changed back and forwards during the year. Life, be in it today, live more of your life.

